<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911126-0131</DOCNO><DOCID>911126-0131.</DOCID><HL>   Canada to Offer Bonds   Totaling $1.58 Billion</HL><DATE>11/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.80billion Canadian dollars (US$1.58 billion) of bonds today.   The offering will include three maturities: 8.25% bondsdue March 1, 1997; 8.5% bonds due April 1, 2002; and 9.25%bonds due June 1, 2022.</LP><TEXT>   The Bank of Canada has agreed to buy C$100 million of thenew bonds. The remainder will be available to the public.   Proceeds of the issue will be used to redeem C$2.08billion of maturing government bonds.</TEXT></DOC>